#' @importFrom SeuratObject CreateSeuratObject
#' @keywords internal
"_PACKAGE"

#' Load the combined 10x Genomics PBMC single-cell reference dataset
#'
#' Loads a processed single-cell RNA-seq reference dataset generated by combining
#' publicly available peripheral blood mononuclear cell (PBMC) datasets from
#' healthy donors provided by 10x Genomics. The reference combines the 6k PBMC,
#' 8k PBMC, and 10k PBMC datasets and was processed, annotated, filtered, and
#' formatted for use in QUASAR deconvolution workflows.
#'
#' The returned object is a processed Seurat object containing 22,629 features
#' across 21,978 cells. The active assay is `RNA`, with 22,629 features and
#' 0 variable features. The assay contains only one layer: `counts`.
#'
#' Cell type annotations are stored in the object metadata column `celltype`.
#' The dataset contains the following annotated cell types:
#'
#' \describe{
#'   \item{Bcells}{3,352 cells}
#'   \item{CD4Tcells}{8,181 cells}
#'   \item{CD8Tcells}{3,329 cells}
#'   \item{Monocytes}{5,428 cells}
#'   \item{NK}{1,586 cells}
#'   \item{Unknown}{102 cells}
#' }
#'
#' Dataset-of-origin information is stored in the metadata column `donor_id`.
#' The combined reference contains:
#'
#' \describe{
#'   \item{pbmc10k}{9,141 cells}
#'   \item{pbmc6k}{4,658 cells}
#'   \item{pbmc8k}{8,179 cells}
#' }
#'
#' The original 10x Genomics datasets are licensed under the Creative Commons
#' Attribution 4.0 International License (CC BY 4.0). The data included here
#' were processed, annotated, filtered, and reformatted by Sergej Ruff. No
#' endorsement by 10x Genomics is implied.
#'
#' @return A processed Seurat object with 22,629 features and 21,978 cells.
#' The object contains one assay, `RNA`, with the layer `counts`. Cell type
#' labels are stored in `celltype`, and dataset-origin labels are stored in
#' `donor_id`.
#'
#' @source
#' 10x Genomics:
#' \itemize{
#'   \item 6k PBMCs from a Healthy Donor, Universal 3' dataset analyzed using Cell Ranger 1.1.0.
#'   \item 8k PBMCs from a Healthy Donor, Universal 3' dataset analyzed using Cell Ranger 2.1.0.
#'   \item 10k PBMCs from a Healthy Donor (v3 chemistry), Universal 3' dataset analyzed using Cell Ranger 3.0.0.
#' }
#'
#' Original datasets: \url{https://www.10xgenomics.com/resources/datasets}
#'
#' License: Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International,
#' \url{https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/}
#'
#' @examples
#' 
#' pbmc_sc_ref <- load_pbmc_sc_ref()
#'
#' pbmc_sc_ref
#'
#' table(pbmc_sc_ref$celltype)
#' table(pbmc_sc_ref$donor_id)
#'
#' @export
load_pbmc_sc_ref <- function() {
  path <- system.file(
    "extdata",
    "pbmc_sc_ref.rds",
    package = "QuasarDeconData",
    mustWork = TRUE
  )

  readRDS(path)
}



#' Processed GSE107011 PBMC bulk deconvolution dataset
#'
#' A processed peripheral blood mononuclear cell (PBMC) bulk RNA-seq
#' deconvolution dataset derived from GEO accession GSE107011. The original
#' study profiled immune cell types and PBMC samples and used the data for
#' transcriptomic characterization and deconvolution analyses.
#'
#' The object is provided as a named list with bulk expression profiles,
#' experimentally derived ground-truth cell type proportions, and gene
#' identifiers. It was processed and formatted for use in QUASAR deconvolution
#' workflows.
#'
#' The object contains the following elements:
#'
#' \describe{
#'   \item{ground_truth_proportions}{
#'     A numeric matrix or data frame with 12 samples and 6 cell type columns.
#'     The columns are `Bcells`, `CD4Tcells`, `CD8Tcells`, `Monocytes`, `NK`,
#'     and `Unknown`.
#'   }
#'   \item{bulk_expression_profiles}{
#'     A numeric matrix or data frame with 36,128 features and 12 bulk PBMC
#'     samples.
#'   }
#'   \item{ensembl_ids}{
#'     Gene identifiers corresponding to the rows of `bulk_expression_profiles`.
#'   }
#' }
#'
#' Ground-truth cell type proportions are available for the following cell
#' types:
#'
#' \describe{
#'   \item{Bcells}{B cells}
#'   \item{CD4Tcells}{CD4 T cells}
#'   \item{CD8Tcells}{CD8 T cells}
#'   \item{Monocytes}{Monocytes}
#'   \item{NK}{Natural killer cells}
#'   \item{Unknown}{Unassigned or remaining cell type fraction}
#' }
#'
#' The data included here were processed and reformatted by Sergej Ruff for use
#' with QUASAR deconvolution workflows. No endorsement by the original data
#' providers is implied.
#'
#' @format A named list with three elements:
#' \describe{
#'   \item{ground_truth_proportions}{
#'     A 12 x 6 matrix or data frame containing ground-truth PBMC cell type
#'     proportions.
#'   }
#'   \item{bulk_expression_profiles}{
#'     A 36,128 x 12 matrix or data frame containing bulk expression profiles.
#'   }
#'   \item{ensembl_ids}{
#'     A vector of Ensembl gene identifiers corresponding to the expression
#'     profile rows.
#'   }
#' }
#'
#' @source
#' Gene Expression Omnibus accession GSE107011:
#' \url{https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/geo/query/acc.cgi?acc=GSE107011}
#'
#' Monaco G, Lee B, Xu W, Mustafah S, Hwang YY, Carré C, Burdin N,
#' Visan L, Ceccarelli M, Poidinger M, Zippelius A, Pedro de Magalhães J,
#' Larbi A. RNA-Seq Signatures Normalized by mRNA Abundance Allow Absolute
#' Deconvolution of Human Immune Cell Types. Cell Reports.
#'
#' @usage data(GSE107011)
#'
#' @keywords datasets
#'
#' @examples
#' data(GSE107011)
#'
#' names(GSE107011)
#' dim(GSE107011$bulk_expression_profiles)
#' dim(GSE107011$ground_truth_proportions)
#' colnames(GSE107011$ground_truth_proportions)
"GSE107011"


